reviews.text:
...beautiful sermon and music rooted in the traditions of great theologians and composers while also respecting the thoughtful that is new.
...gently-friendly congregation, too : )
A surprisingly non-judgmental church that does a lot of loving Mission work. Solid, scripture based teaching and the music is fantastic. Friendly folks, too.
Great place for meetings
Went to a DAR meeting.
Got kicked out
A very cool museum located in East Greenwich. Worth the trip, but it is only open June, July and August on Saturday & Sunday 1-4 pm.
Well preserved, beautiful home.  Gardens are pretty
Very nice piece of history

This is a great opportunity to see one of the 18 militia Armories in the state. This is still a working facility under the control of the Original residents The Kentish Guard oozing with Rhode Island history and tradition.
Gman
Muskets are high powered military grade killing machines. They’re responsible for millions of senseless deaths. Ban muskets now!
Awesome Rhode Island history
This is absolutely one of the Nation's best collection of rare historical weapons and militia historical pieces.

The most extensive collection of firearms and militaria under one roof. I particularly enjoyed how they have artifacts from every conflict together in their respective rooms. Of interest also is the underground rifle range in the basement which goes under Main Street. Follow their website or FB page as they have many tours and events, mostly free!
Great space for a party. However the person in charge of booking was very rude.
It's a beautiful time and lots to see
Nice place,  good for weddings
Always great food and drinks. Regan is the best! I know my burger will be cooked right every time. If you haven't eaten here you're missing out!

My go-to pizza place. The cheese pizza, buffalo chicken pizza, and veggie pizza are all really good. Had the veggie pizza last night and it was piled sky high with fresh veggies. Ordering for pick up is always ready really quickly.

Food was alright. Online ordering didn't have as many options as I wanted. Wanted fried chicken in my calzone and they only offered grilled. Was fine, but when they came with delivery, they told me they forgot the mozzarella sticks. They offered me $6 back because they are $5.99. I didn't feel up for a fight over my food, they should have offered my $2 tip back and $2 delivery fee, if not given me the whole thing free. My roommate and I are now still hungry and can either reorder food or go out to get food (which was the whole point of ordering food in the first place)

We’ve been to the EG location 20 plus times over the last 5 years. Pizza is usually very good. Burgers are good. Just be aware if you go on a Friday or Saturday night before 8 its like romper room. For some reason its full of families with kids under 10. Very loud. Picture chuckie cheese without the ball pit.

Delicious food. Cool atmosphere. Good service.  We visited on my birthday on our way to Newport. I ordered a chicken sandwich. It had great ingredients, would have been nice to have had a full breast for chicken instead of just a half. We were in a little bit of a hurry, the service took a bit longer than expected as there was only one person serving the dining room. Over all, the place is aesthetically pleasing, food was yummy, great location.
Great atmosphere! Happy hour was amazing. The staff are lovely. Good value for the cost. Food was delicious and the drinks were strong!!! Will go again!

We went as a big group, 14 people for a birthday party for two kids. The staff was very friendly. Since we booked for the hibachi, they called many times to remind us to be on time. We had never been here before and the chefs put on a great show. The food was delicious as well!

This is a delicious and fancy place  my fiance and I have made it our go to place for delicious sushi and for her vegan options as well nice staff great food normal price and awesome atmosphere. All around a 10/10 highly recommend it
First time hibachi. Had a wonderful experience. Food was great, waitress was on point, hibachi chef was funny and engaging. Definitely would go back and recommend to others
This is where I go when I want to have an awesome meal.  I love the way they have the restaurant laid out.  You can either order from the menu or get food off the habachi.  Always entertaining.

Absolutely fantastic and even better now that they accept credit cards. If you haven't tried their corned beef hash, you need to try some soon.  This restaurant has been a staple of Main Street for more than 30 years
Very good comfort food. Great hash and red potatoes.  You feel like your home there.
Eat here every week and everything is awsome and most important delicous. The waitresses are friendly and top shelf. Awsome service.
One of my favorite breakfast joints. The corned beef hash is excellent
Small place, standard breakfast menu, prices are very reasonable.  Corn Beef hash was great.  Had eggs Benedict special that was excellent.
Great martinis! Awesome fries and meals.
Tiramisu martini is heavenly and pineapple upside down cake martini is amazing
Couldn't wait for this ice cream store to open , I love the mocha cappuccino  soft serve ! It's  a good old fashioned ice cream store , great service
Greatest ice cream shop in the county run by the friendliest people

Busy place in summer. Lots of flavors to choose from. I have fructose intolerance and my nutritionist called to ask if it's in the ice cream. They couldn't have been any nicer, giving us the information where it's made, etc.  and now I know what I can and cannot have which is great. Kudos to them for that.
One of the best places to get icecream
Awesome flavors of icecream, soft serve, and comes. Keep up the good work! 👍
Curran Keough is best of the best. He makes house hunting a positive experience and has a lot of valuable knowledge. He understands the market and delivers great customer service.

New Years Eve 2018 - called in an order for pick-up 'round 5p.m., told it would be ready in 40 minutes.  Arrived at the time stated to find the place is mobbed with people waiting, OK I think - running a little bit late, after all, it is a holiday, but......... No orders coming out, angry people around me who had called in hours before - one even ordered online the day before!!!!!  When I heard all of the complaints from people waiting, I left, thinking it was a lost cause.  Cathy Garden, you lost a customer forever.  If you can't fill the orders, you are overwhelmed, or understaffed - DON"T take anymore orders, you fools.  I will spread the word that Cathy Garden sucks.

Update - almost one month later: no response to my review, Cathy garden????  No explanation, no apology???  All those customers waiting anf you continued to take more orders???  I guess you just don't care - most merchants and business owners would respond and try to save custom.  I will double down on warning people off Cathy Gardens.  Sucks!!!

It was a very good experience. Unlike usual Chinese buffet, there were fewer items. But whatever was there was tasty, well-cooked, and fresh. It was clear that they cared about the quality of their buffet items, instead of having too many items that are not satisfactory. The items were being refilled regularly. The hosts and staff were very nice.
I’ve been eating here 25+  years. Never once disappointed. Great staff too!
Been going there for 40 years. Always hot and fresh, Joe is the best and so are all the employees! PS. And I'm only 47, lol
Awesome fresh food and friendly staff

The busboy ( I had the same job in 1972) insisted on cleaning our table and made everyone uncomfortable too soon after we finished our meal. We ask for the leftover food portion of my elderly father to be saved and it wasn't.  The portions of food are very generous but, the food was less than spectacular. This isn't the first place I would consider again. eating out.
Exceptional service!! Great food!! Even the manager stopped by or table to see how everything was going. A little pricey,  but worth it. Loved the freshly made pasta

Highly recommend this place!  I’ve been several times and it does not disappoint. Portions are huge. Drinks are great. The Italian wedding soup was amazing. I had the Ribeye and it was a fantastic cut!  This place won’t disappoint!

Food and wait staff were good. Hostess was chit chatting while we stood there for 5 minutes waiting to be seated. Also, there was an issue with a gift card which was more than likely not activated properly by one of their employees in the first place and the manager was not helpful at all alleviating the situation. I can think of better places to go spend $100. Won't be back.

We we're a party of six at 8:00 o'clock. We were seated promptly. Cozy interior recently renovated. Large bar in the center of the room. Can't wait for warmer weather to sit out on the patio area which has an amazing gas fireplace and beautiful stone work. So we ordered the Chicken Parmesan with a bottle of Pinot noir called Contour. The food was excellent and the wine went perfectly. Also have to mention our Server Kaitlyn. She was the best. Very attentive and always near. Outstanding service. We will all definitely return and we hope to see Kaitlyn again. Highly recommend the Safehouse. Very reasonably priced.

Under new management since the last time we were here. Decor changed some but still comfy. Service friendly and helpful. Good food menu and good tasting. But like a lot of places no interest in keeping up with changes in the beer menu

We've come here a couple times now when we are in the area. They have a great selection of local beer which is nice being able try something new when you're coming from out of state. Their menu has a wide variety of options that are reasonably priced. Their burgers are one of the bigger options which makes making a decision very difficult because they all sound really good. The wait staff is knowledgeable and polite each time we come. I suspect we'll return again in the future with out hesitation.
Food was good and staff were very nice people. I recommend it for date night or a work dinner or a family gathering. Will enjoy their higher quality dishes.

Love this restaurant so much!  We had the Brussels sprouts and hummus plate for apps.  They were amazing! The salmon was cooked and seasoned perfect!  So fresh!!!   The decor is warm and inviting!  Their server was so friendly!  Hands down favorite!
Excellent food and drinks. Good atmosphere. In the summer, they open up their big windows to the street and it makes for a really enjoyable experience.

Excellent great food great service

Thank you very much we had an amazing experience here and the food was amazing. We had great Service, If you want to be treated like a valued guest this is the spot for you. I would highly recommend this restaurant to anyone looking for a solid meal. You did not feel rushed you could enjoy your meal. The food was delicious, and the prices are reasonable as well. We will be returning soon.

Just getting around to describing the experience. Came in for my two year anniversary. Service was attentive and food was great. However they placed us at a table that was less than half the size of every other table around us that was located less than two feet from the couple next to us. Looking around, EVERYONE had a nice luxurious space by comparison. Like literally every other table I spotted had at least 4 feet around them and was a normal size. Our table was very obviously set up to maximize their tables on Valentine's Day, and we spent our dinner being passed on all sides by servers. It's disheartening to make reservations at an "upscale" location paying 50 bucks a person to not even be able to talk to my girlfriend across the table from me with any shred of privacy. Shame on you Eleven Forty Nine, would not recommend.

I took my bestie to 1149 for a Birthday Brunch.  Our server Melissa was very nice and checked on us often but not too often nor not enough....she was perfect.  However, the brunch costs 31.95 per person.  At that cost everything should be fresh.  Eggs were powdered and even the omelet I ordered, which came nice and hot was powdered eggs.  I don't think the cost matches the food.

Outstanding dinning experience whether for lunch or dinner you can't go wrong.  Friendly and attentive staff, outstanding food and reasonably priced.  I have been there for private functions as well as on y own and have never been disappointed always hits the mark which is tough in the restaurant business.  Well done and worth a visit any time.. great place to take clients for a drink and apps also!!!

Eleven Forty Nine pulls out all the stops with their super delicious lobster risotto, big portion, lots of seafood and generally amazing flavor. The bar menu is excellent and this is a great place to take someone for a somewhat special occasion, either business, romance or just a special weekend.

We had the calamari and seared tuna appetizers, which with both packed full of flavor and came out quickly. We had a somewhat large group, and were impressed by the service, especially the speed that everything came out and the fact that our drinks were never empty.

Beer selection here is good, with a couple of good go to flavors for almost any pallet, though I can’t comment on the wine and I unfortunately didn’t make it to dessert, as I was quite thoroughly stuffed after the main entree!

This would be a great place to take a date if you’re looking to impress, or for any slightly more upscale dinners!
Such an incredibly friendly and helpful staff who go above and beyond. Kudos to Mark and Maureen and all the lovely people who work here!

I haven't had a worse post office experience. Words cannot describe the resentment I feel towards USPS after my visit here. I went in excited to mail off my package. I brought a sharpie and scribbled out the old shipping label just so there wouldn't be any confusion. I take it up to the front counter and tell the lady I need to send this off. She then just looks at me as if I had just spilled a bucket boiling water on her and run over her dog in front of her. 

Confused, I ask, "Can you help me with that?" She responds, "Do you even know where it's going?" I say, "Yes." She asks for the zipcode and I tell it to her. 
She then instructs me to put duct tape over the old shipping label and write where it's from and then in the other corner where it's going. So I did. And then brought my package to the counter again. She turns it on it's side and faces it to me.
She then asks very rudely as if I was a brainless baboon trying to get through kindergarten, "Does this look right to you?"
I respond, "Looks fine to me." She then chastizes me because the way I wrote it will make it end up where I'm trying to send it from. Keep in mind I did exactly what she told me to do. Then she tells me I need a shipping label. So I asked, if they print shipping labels. She tells me they don't. So I left and went up the block to UPS and received excellent customer service. And they printed a shipping label for me.
From this day forward I will now be boycotting USPS and I would encourage all to do the same.

ugh I sell on etsy and twice shipped about 10 packages that were prelabeled/prepaid.  They have huge bin you put prelabeled/prepaid items in.  Each time there were several items that arrived to the buyers broken.  I do this every week, so although I am aware they could have broken at other stops, they were going to different parts of the country and the one thing they all had in common was this post office.  One box of Corningware was completely smashed.  I have never seen anything like it.   Every once in a while when I ship from other post offices, one or two items every three or four months might arrive broken, so this was definitely not normal.  The folks at my post office in Warwick are really nice, why so surly at this office?  I also ship from Franklin, where I work and they are SO FRIENDLY!  Franklin also has a bin and it's very rare that something is broken that is shipped from that office.  I pay a ton to wrap in bubble wrap and packing peanuts so they must have really done a number on my packages.  Hateful.
Mark helped me with my packages. He is always very friendly and helpful.

Literally the worst post office ever. The mail carriers refuse to deliver packages to my door. They all cover for each other so if one screws up they won’t even let you tell a supervisor. Supposedly the reason they can’t deliver packages to my door is because of my dog. A 20lb chihuahua mix who is INSIDE ALL DAY. So I requested online for a package to be held at the post office so I could pick it up in a timely manner, instead of waiting for them to tell me at 5 pm that it wouldn’t be delivered and I would have to pick it up the next day. Simple right? You can’t do your job so I’ll do it for you.

What happens? I get an email saying it’s out for delivery. I didn’t even know it was possible to be this bad at a job. Thanks guys.
Couldn't wait for this ice cream store to open , I love the mocha cappuccino  soft serve ! It's  a good old fashioned ice cream store , great service
Greatest ice cream shop in the county run by the friendliest people

Busy place in summer. Lots of flavors to choose from. I have fructose intolerance and my nutritionist called to ask if it's in the ice cream. They couldn't have been any nicer, giving us the information where it's made, etc.  and now I know what I can and cannot have which is great. Kudos to them for that.
One of the best places to get icecream
Awesome flavors of icecream, soft serve, and comes. Keep up the good work! 👍

3 stars is the middle ground because they DO NOT toast bagels, even when you ask for it extra toasted. The inside isn't even toasted, just warmed up. I've had to go back every single time to ask for it more toasted even when I say to make it look brown. Thankfully so far the employees have been incredibly nice every time I have to go back.
The staff are very nice. They make my coffee perfect everytime
Great location. Easy in and out.  Never get your order wrong.
Love the bacon egg on cheese on a plain bagel 🥯

Didn't have the 13 cents change to complete the transaction for a donut and coffee, so I offered a twenty. She saw my Vietnam veteran hat and said, "The donut's on the house. Thank you for your service," handing me back a dollar and some  change. I thanked her and put the dollar under tip jar.

As soon as I walked in, I was greeted with a happy smile! Although when it came time to order, I had to wait since there was only one person working the cash register (even though there were a lot more behind the register area although I am not sure what they were doing). I got the broccoli cheddar soup which was of course delicious and I sat by the fire. It was peaceful. I will definitely come back to this panera in the future!

They rarely get orders correct. Today my salad was missing the chicken, they asked if I wanted to come back to get it, really! Don't they teach their folks that prepare the food to actually read their computer screens? They managed to not put the red onion on the salad but no chicken.

We order from Panera on Reed Hartman regularly for our company lunches. Have always loved the food. Last time we ordered, there was a hair in one of our soups. Two of us ordered the same soup. Needless to say it really made our stomachs churn and ruined lunch for all five of us that had ordered. I called to speak to a manager. The woman that answered the phone was beyond rude. She had no idea what I was calling for and said "they too busy to speak to you". Mind you, I could have been calling for catering info because I had not given my reason for calling yet. When I insisted on needing to speak to a manager, the delivery manager got on the phone. I explained everything. She apologized and said "Your next delivery order will be comped. I'm putting it in the book." (I didn't ask her to do this.) So we called today to order and spoke to the delivery manager who said she could only comp the cup of soup. Since that is not what she told me, I asked to speak to the GM who proceeded to say that they can only comp the soup. I asked if they record their calls -- they don't. Picture of the hair in the soup below. They need to learn about good customer service because we ordered regularly from them not only for a few of us but for team lunches to be catered in as well and we will not be doing that anymore. I don't normally complain. I never leave bad reviews but this is ridiculous. I didn't ask for our entire order to be comped, they volunteered it and then didn't honor it.

Outstanding experience during the lunch rush.

The line was to the door, but the staff and management kept the service flowing and my food came out perfect.

Very nice facility with plenty of seating, much above average for a Panera. Well maintained and clean.
This is an ok Panera Bread. It's pretty much what you would expect. The place is nice, clean and the staff is friendly. Other than that there is nothing too special about the place.

Love walking into a Starbucks and smelling the fresh coffee. This location was clean and the staff friendly. Coffee was made to order and correctly made for this picky coffee drinker lol. This spot has an area for when you are wanting to socialize or break out the computer/books and do some studying while sipping on a latte. Only problem I seen was the drive through and parking area are very tight but couldn't take a star away just for that. Keep it up at this location cause my little girl and I will definitely be back for our coffee.
Always fast, friendly, and informative! Their coffee is great and their snacks are always yummy! Mobile pickup through their app is always very convenient as well!

Yummy but prices need to stop going up, they  are beyond being a very successful business that has millions of people addicted and stopping for ine of their many yummy beverages and foods almost every day like its crack, stop being greedy with the cost increase of everything, PLEASE. I want to be able to afford my coffee "crack" lol just playing, kinda. Attention there's no illegal drugs served at any Starbucks facility
... that I'm aware of!
Very friendly service. Got the order correct. Fast.
Rude, impersonal staff, slow service, dirty restrooms. The food is blah, you get better quality food at much lower prices at McDonalds or any of the other fast food chains in the area.
